import cv2
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Function to distort an image (apply random perspective distortion)
def distort_image(image):
    h, w = image.shape[:2]
    
    # Random distortion by moving corners slightly
    src_points = np.array([[0, 0], [w-100, 0], [w-10, h-100], [100, h-100]], dtype=np.float32)
    dst_points = src_points + np.random.randint(-160,50, size=src_points.shape).astype(np.float32)
    
    # Apply distortion to the image
    matrix = cv2.getPerspectiveTransform(src_points, dst_points)
    distorted_image = cv2.warpPerspective(image, matrix, (w, h))
    
    return distorted_image, src_points, dst_points
In [131]:
# Function for bilinear interpolation (as before)
def bilinear_interpolation(src_img, src_points, dst_points):
    h, w = src_img.shape[:2]
    matrix, status = cv2.findHomography(src_points, dst_points)
    rectified_img = cv2.warpPerspective(src_img, matrix, (w, h), flags=cv2.INTER_LINEAR)
    return rectified_img
In [132]:
# Helper function to display images
def display_images(original, distorted, rectified, title1="Original Image", title2="Distorted Image", title3="Rectified Image"):
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 5))
    
    plt.subplot(1, 3, 1)
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(original, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(title1)
    
    plt.subplot(1, 3, 2)
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(distorted, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(title2)
    
    plt.subplot(1, 3, 3)
    plt.imshow(cv2.cvtColor(rectified, cv2.COLOR_BGR2RGB))
    plt.title(title3)
    
    plt.show()

  • Objective: The task aimed to rectify geometric distortions in satellite imagery.
  • Steps Taken:
    • The original image was distorted using random perspective warping.
    • The distorted image was rectified using bilinear interpolation and a homography matrix based on control points.
  • Results: The rectified image closely resembled the original satellite image. Minor pixel variations were observed due to interpolation.
  • Challenges: Identifying precise GCPs is crucial, especially for large-scale satellite images with terrain variation.
